fix: resolve 9 upstream issues (#188, #182, #191, #160, #135, #164, #165, #102, #155)

Addresses the following open issues from sc0ty/subsync:

- #188: Last subtitle line timestamp extending to end of video
  Clamp subtitle durations after transform_framerate to prevent
  events from stretching to absurd lengths (3x original or 30s max).

- #182/#97: 'Invalid output pattern' when filenames contain braces
  Unknown {variables} in output patterns are now escaped and treated
  as literal text instead of raising a KeyError.

- #191: CLI mode spawns a visible console window on Windows
  Only call AllocConsole when stdout is not already writable, and
  prefer AttachConsole to the parent process first.

- #160: No error message when CLI sync fails (not enough points)
  Print the actual vs required point count and suggest --effort=1.0
  --min-points-no=2 as a workaround for difficult files.

- #135: No way to Ctrl+C and save partial result in CLI
  SIGINT handler now saves synchronized subtitles if correlation
  was already achieved before terminating.

- #164: Small offset (<2s) subtitles fail to synchronize
  Lower default minPointsNo from 20 to 10 so near-perfect subs
  can lock in with fewer correlation points.

- #165: No default language setting or default view mode
  Add defaultSubLang, defaultRefLang, and defaultView settings.
  Languages fall back to defaults when no last-used value exists.
  defaultView='batch' starts in batch mode by default.

- #102: No taskbar progress indicator on Windows
  SyncWin now updates the Windows taskbar progress via ITaskbarList3
  COM interface (gracefully degrades if comtypes unavailable).

- #155: Incomplete documentation
  Comprehensive README rewrite with CLI reference, batch patterns,
  configuration guide, supported formats/languages, and build guide.
